	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Sacrament of Penance</h1>
	
	<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
		<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
		<div id="contentSub"><span class="mw-redirectedfrom">&#160;&#160;(Redirected from <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Sacrament_of_Penance_(Catholic_Church)&amp;redirect=no" class="mw-redirect" title="Sacrament of Penance (Catholic Church)">Sacrament of Penance (Catholic Church)</a>)</span></div>
		
		
		<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="Sacrament_of_Penance_(Catholic_Church)#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="Sacrament_of_Penance_(Catholic_Church)#p-search">Jump to search</a>
		<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">This article is about one of the sacraments of the Catholic Church. For confession in other religions, see <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Confession_(disambiguation)" class="mw-disambig" title="Confession (disambiguation)">Confession (disambiguation)</a>. For penance in other religions, see <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Penance" title="Penance">Penance</a>. For reconciliation in other religions, see <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reconciliation_(theology)" title="Reconciliation (theology)">Reconciliation (theology)</a>.</div>
